      <div class="content-section"><div class="section-header"><span class="section-tag">Overview</span><h2>What Are ELSS Mutual Funds?</h2></div>
        <p>Equity Linked Savings Scheme (ELSS) is a type of mutual fund that qualifies for income tax deduction under Section 80C of the Income Tax Act, up to ₹1.5 lakh per financial year. ELSS funds invest predominantly in equity and equity-related instruments, providing the dual benefit of tax savings and wealth creation through stock market exposure.</p>
        <p>ELSS has the shortest lock-in period (3 years) among all Section 80C instruments — compared to 5 years for tax-saving FDs, 15 years for PPF, and 5 years for NSC. This shorter lock-in, combined with equity market exposure, makes ELSS the most efficient tax-saving instrument for investors willing to accept market risk.</p>
        <p>Over the past decade, top ELSS funds have delivered 13%–16% CAGR — significantly outperforming PPF (7.1%), tax-saving FDs (6%–7%), and NSC (7.7%). For an investor in the 30% tax bracket, the combined benefit of ₹46,800 tax saved plus 14% equity returns makes ELSS the undisputed champion of tax-saving investments.</p>
      </div>

